    scenario_context: 'Instagram has 2 billion monthly active users and generates roughly 30% of Meta\'s total revenue through advertising. Reels crossed 200 billion plays per day in 2023, but internal data shows that time-spent growth has stalled in the 18-24 cohort over the past three quarters. TikTok has 1.5 billion MAUs globally, BeReal had a brief cultural moment in 2022-23, and YouTube Shorts is at 70 billion daily views. The creator monetization gap between Instagram and TikTok narrowed significantly after Meta launched the Reels Play bonus program.',
    scenario_trigger: 'The head of Instagram product asks for a frank threat assessment before a strategy offsite — specifically, which external or internal dynamic poses the greatest existential risk to Instagram in the next 18 months.',
    scenario_question: 'What is the single biggest threat to Instagram, and what makes it structurally more dangerous than the alternatives?',
    engineer_standout: 'Distinguishes between competitive threats (which Instagram can counter with product investment) and structural threats (which are embedded in platform dynamics and cannot be countered through features alone).',
