    title: "Meta CEO's Top 3 Priorities for the Next 5 Years",
    scenario_role: 'staff engineer',
    scenario_context: 'Meta generated $134B in revenue in 2023, with 98% from advertising, primarily on Facebook and Instagram. The Reality Labs division has lost over $40B since 2021 with no clear path to profitability. AI infrastructure investment is accelerating — Meta spent $35B in capex in 2023 and announced plans for $65B in 2024. WhatsApp has 2.5 billion users but minimal direct monetization. The regulatory environment in Europe is constraining targeted advertising, and the US antitrust case over the Instagram and WhatsApp acquisitions is ongoing.',
    scenario_trigger: 'A board member asks for a frank 5-year strategic prioritization before the annual board meeting — specifically, which three bets should define how Meta allocates capital, talent, and CEO attention.',
    scenario_question: 'If you were setting Meta\'s top three strategic priorities for the next five years, what would they be and how would you rank them?',
    engineer_standout: 'Recognizes the tension between advertising dependence (90-day pressure) and platform-layer bets (5-year horizon), and identifies that the CEO priority list must explicitly sequence these rather than treating them as parallel.',
